# Wrap-Up Routine

When the user asks to "wrap up", "wrap up for today", or says they are ready to close the app, make the workspace safe to close without losing work.

Follow this checklist:
- Verify git status and summarize any uncommitted, untracked, or unpushed work.
- Save necessary project state by committing/pushing only when the user requested it or an existing workflow rule requires it.
- If a deploy was performed, follow the deploy workflow rule and push the deployed committed code to `main`.
- Stop local dev servers and long-running watchers for this project, including Vite, Storybook, and related preview/studio processes.
- Leave unrelated user changes untouched; do not discard or reset anything.
- Report final status clearly: deploy URLs if relevant, commit/push status, stopped servers, remaining risks or manual follow-ups.
